Introduction

Q

What is the Validator / Purchasing Team's role in the GMS?

A

The GMS helps the Validation and Purchasing Teams efficiently review and validate gate pass requests for the movement of materials, equipment, or supplies. It ensures all items leaving or entering the premises are properly authorized and recorded.

As a Validator or Purchasing Team member you can:

‚ñ∏

Review submitted gate pass requests for accuracy and completeness.

‚ñ∏

Approve or reject requests based on documentation and purchase orders.

‚ñ∏

Ensure compliance with company policies for material movement.

‚ñ∏

Monitor the flow of goods for safety and accountability.

Login

Q

How do I log in as a Validator?

A
1

Go to the Gate Pass Management System (GMS) website.

2

Enter your Username and Password (e.g., validator1).

3

Click Submit.

4

Upon success you will see "Welcome to Gatepass System" and your landing page will display all requests pending validation.

Login Page ‚Äî Validator Credentials
Landing Page ‚Äî All For-Validation Requests

Review Request

Q

How do I review a submitted gate pass request?

A

After logging in, all requests with status FOR-VALIDATION will appear in your Gate Passes list. To review a request:

1

Find the request in the Gate Passes table.

2

Click the View (eye) icon to open the Gatepass Request Details modal.

3

Verify all information: Control No., Appointment Schedule & Time, Gate Access, Company, Drivers (license validity, vehicle, plate number, LTO validity), Visitors, Purposes & Justifications, Person to Meet, Department, and current approval statuses.

4

Check that all approval rows show the correct pending status before proceeding.

Review Request ‚Äî Gatepass Request Details Modal

Gate Passes List ‚Äî Action Buttons for Validator
Q

How do I submit a validated request for approval?

A
1

After reviewing the request and confirming all details are correct, click the Submit (send/arrow) icon in the Actions column.

2

A pop-up confirmation will appear asking: "Are you sure you want to submit this gatepass?"

3

Click Yes to confirm, or No to cancel.

4

Once submitted, the request status changes to SUBMITTED and only the View button remains ‚Äî the request can no longer be edited or cancelled.

Submit Confirmation Pop-up & Submitted Status
Q

What if there are errors in the request?

A

If you find any errors or missing information before submitting, click the Edit (pencil) icon to open the request in edit mode. Make the necessary corrections and click Update to save changes. You can then proceed to submit the corrected request for approval. If the request cannot be validated at all, use the Cancel button to reject it.

View Approved Request

Q

What happens after I submit a validated request?

A

Once validated and submitted, the request is forwarded to the WFS third-party approval system and must pass through the full approval chain before it is fully approved:

1

Validated By ‚Äî The Validator confirms the request (your role).

2

Recommending Approval ‚Äî Reviews and recommends the request.

3

Approved By ‚Äî Authorizes entry/exit of people, vehicles, or materials.

4

Final Approval By ‚Äî Final sign-off for full authorization.

The request cannot proceed at any stage until each approver has signed off. Once fully approved, the status shows APPROVED.

Q

What does a fully approved gate pass form look like?

A

The approved Gatepass Request Details modal shows the complete printed form with status APPROVED, including: Philsaga Mining Corporation / MMPR header, appointment schedule and time, gate access points, company contact details, driver and vehicle information (with LTO validity), visitors list, purposes and justifications, person to meet and department, and the full signature row showing Processed By, Validated By, Recommending Approval, and Approved By. The form also includes visitor DO's and DON'Ts reminders at the bottom.

Approved Gate Pass ‚Äî Full View Form
Q

Can I access Reports from the Validator dashboard?

A

Yes. The Validator dashboard navigation includes a Reports menu item in addition to Home. This gives the Purchasing Team access to reporting features not available to regular Department Users. Click Reports in the top navigation bar to access available reports.
